ield. The Uncaring, Intricate World concludes with afterwords by Jane I. Guyer and Julie Livingston, who critically reflect on its context, its meaning for today, and relevance to conducting anthropological work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aAnthropologistsvDiaries. 0aChildrenzZambezi River ValleyxSocial conditions. 0aEconomic developmentxPolitical aspectszZambezi River Valley. 0aEconomic developmentxSocial aspectszZambezi River Valley. 0aTonga (Zambezi people)xSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aMeyers, Todd, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478005520zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478005520423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478005520.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles